cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses crafting adversarial examples in the image domain, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves theoretical analysis and empirical studies, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper proposes a black-box attack method that encodes the adversarial example searching problem as a derivative-free optimization problem, which involves optimization techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories.
